Phase 7 #5 — user picks from queued candidates (vitest infrastructure live; TDD mandatory per Rule 25)

Phase 7 #4 shipped on 2026-05-16 as `2cdc3c3`:
- New PasswordResetToken Prisma model + migration `20260515162430_add_password_reset_tokens` applied to yelli_dev
- passwordSchema extracted in @yelli/shared (reused by register + reset)
- requestPasswordReset + resetPassword tRPC procedures with security defaults locked: 1h TTL, single-use, sha256-only storage, no enumeration, security_version++ on reset, rate-limited both endpoints
- email.ts lazy nodemailer wrapper (MailHog fallback in dev); pinned nodemailer to ^6.9.16 for Auth.js v5 peer compat
- forgot-password page wired to mutation (TODO replaced)
- New /reset-password/[token] server + client form using shadcn Form + RHF + Zod (UI Rule #4)
- 8 new test cases bringing the suite to 20/20 in 313ms
- 4 new lessons documented: prisma migrate dev DATABASE_URL gap, nodemailer/Auth.js peer pin, vi.mock @/env extension, separate password_reset_tokens table rationale
- Visual QA Rule 16 deferred — public auth pages (/forgot-password + /reset-password) pending manual smoke on next dev-up

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Candidates (any order, user picks):
----------------------------------------------------------------------

(c) JWT org-slug encoding                   [middleware foundation — high-risk]
    Scope: Tier 3 (~10 files, middleware + auth.config + session callback + all consumers)
    - apps/web/src/server/auth.config.ts — add `organization_slug` to JWT
    - apps/web/src/server/auth.ts — populate from session.user
    - apps/web/src/middleware.ts — resolve tenant from JWT, validate URL ↔ session match (security.md TENANT MIDDLEWARE SAFETY)
    - Test: middleware unit test for tenant-switch attack rejection
    Risk: every authenticated route depends on this; reserve for careful fresh-context session
    Tier 3 → mandatory split via memory-governance §1: probably 3 sub-sessions (auth.config + auth.ts → middleware → consumers).

(d) join/[token] tRPC                       [needs LiveKit ⏳ for full integration]
    Unit tests OK against mocked LiveKit token mint; integration deferred until LIVEKIT_API_KEY filled
    Existing getJoinToken in meetingsRouter has 0 test coverage — could pair with this if scope allows

(e) Socket.IO auth middleware               [depends on (c)]
    Should land AFTER (c) so the JWT contract is stable

(f) Root landing page                       [verify scope first]
    Current /page.tsx is 11 lines — check PRODUCT.md for what's expected
    Likely Tier 1

(g) Coverage threshold gate                 [housekeeping — ~1 file]
    `vitest run --coverage` works (20 tests cover authRouter.register + authRouter.requestPasswordReset + authRouter.resetPassword + meetingsRouter.create)
    No minimum % gate yet — add to vitest.config.ts and CI workflow
    Should land before Phase 8 — quick win to lock the safety net

(h) NEW: Tighten request-password-reset rate limiting   [hardening — ~2 files]
    Currently uses rateLimiters.auth (in-memory LRU, ~5/min per IP+key).
    Could add a per-user 24h cap (e.g. ≤5 reset emails per user per day) to prevent
    a targeted user from receiving spam reset emails when an attacker repeatedly
    fires off the endpoint. Cost: another small Prisma query per request.
    Tests would assert the cap engages at request #6 (returns ok still — no enumeration — but
    skips email send + token mint).

(i) NEW: Periodic cleanup of expired/consumed password_reset_tokens
    A BullMQ scheduled job to DELETE consumed tokens > 30 days old and unconsumed
    expired tokens > 7 days. Keeps the table from growing unboundedly.
    Pairs with the Coverage gate (g) — both are housekeeping.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Rule 25 reminder for ALL of the above:
  → Write failing test FIRST (RED), then implementation (GREEN), then refactor.
  → Test patterns: [[trpc-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #2) + [[meetings-protected-route-test]] (Phase 7 #3) + [[trpc-test-with-env-mock]] (Phase 7 #4).
  → For forms: reuse the [[shadcn-form-primitive]] pattern from Phase 7 #3 (`_meeting-form.tsx` and `_reset-form.tsx` as reference impls).
  → For shared schemas: `<Entity>CreateClientInputSchema` for client-facing input, `<Entity>CreateInputSchema` for admin/internal projection.
  → For new env vars consumed by routers: add `vi.mock("@/env", ...)` to the test file (extends Phase 7 #4 pattern).

Recommended next: (g) Coverage threshold gate — quick housekeeping win that locks the test safety net before Phase 8. The 20-test suite is currently lint-and-pray; one accidental skip(skip)(skip) and we'd never notice. Then (h) hardening of request-password-reset before (c) JWT middleware (which is the riskiest open ticket).

Pending Rule 16 follow-up: smoke-test /app/meetings/new in browser after next `pnpm dev` up (Phase 7 #3 carryover). NEW: also smoke-test /forgot-password + /reset-password/[token] — public routes, no credentials needed.
